items.title: TCS Q4 FY25 – Is it worth a look post the U-turn on US tariff?
items.description: Upside triggers are missing, but downside looks limited despite volatility

items.title: Apollo Hospitals planning buyouts to boost North India footprint
items.description: Apollo is also planning to build a $29 million cancer center, and sees oncology, cardiac, neurology and preventive health care as key pillars of growth, Reddy said.

items.title: Indian medical device makers prepare for US push, sensing opportunity from China tariffs
items.description: Some of the India medical devices companies have started work on regulatory filings and paperwork, to ensure they do not miss out on the opportunity emerging out of this tariff war.
